    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using `vim.treesitter.query.set()` with `inherits` modeline, it uses the specified query but base query is ignored.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Save the following snippet as `minimal.lua`:\n\n```lua\nlocal repro_file = vim.fn.fnamemodify(vim.fn.expand('%'), ':p')\nlocal repro_path = vim.fn.fnamemodify(repro_file, ':h')\nlocal injection_query_path = repro_path .. '/queries/custom/injections.scm'\n\nif vim.fn.filereadable(injection_query_path) == 0 then\n  -- === INJECTED ===\n  local repro_query = [[\n    (variable_declaration\n      (assignment_statement\n        (variable_list\n          name: (identifier) @_query\n          (#eq? @_query \"repro_query\"))\n        (expression_list\n          value: (string\n            content: (string_content) @injection.content)))\n      (#set! injection.language \"query\"))\n  ]]\n\n  vim.fn.mkdir(repro_path .. '/queries/custom', 'p')\n  vim.fn.writefile(vim.fn.split(repro_query, '\\n'), injection_query_path, 's')\nend\n\nvim.opt.rtp:append(repro_path)\n\n-- === BUG ===\nvim.treesitter.query.set('lua', 'injections', '; inherits: lua,custom')\n\n-- === NO INJECTIONS  ===\nvim.treesitter.query.set(\n  'c',\n  'injections',\n  [[; inherits: c\n    (identifier) @spell]]\n)\n\n-- === NO INJECTIONS ===\nvim.cmd('highlight Normal guibg=#0a0a0a')\nvim.cmd('highlight Number guifg=#3ddbd9')\nvim.cmd('highlight Statement guifg=#be95ff gui=NONE')\nvim.cmd('highlight Type guifg=#08bdba')\nvim.cmd('highlight @variable.member guifg=#78a9ff')\n```\n\n2. Run:\n\n```bash\nnvim --clean -u minimal.lua\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nBuilt-in `lua` injections should not be ignored, in this case:\n- `vim.treesitter.query.set()`\n- `vim.cmd()`\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.5\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux Mint 21.2 Cinnamon \n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\n`nvim-linux-x86_64.appimage` from release page",
